"AMERSHAM, with its stately church, cobble-paved streets, quaint inns and gabled houses, retains the tranquillity of bygone days. The Town Hall, a solid building with arched and pillared basement, was built in 1682 at the charges of Sir William Drake to whom the picturesque Alms-houses, with their quaint doorways and diamond paned-windows are also due. In Amersham Church, John Knox and Richard Baxter have preached, whilst near by is the spot where numerous adherents to the Protestant faith were burnt at the stake,"